    <refnamediv>
      <refname>mail::account::isRemoteUrl</refname>
      <refpurpose>Determine whether the account is a remote account</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>

    <refsynopsisdiv>
      <literallayout>
&libmail-includemail;
</literallayout>

      <funcsynopsis>
	<funcprototype>
	  <funcdef>bool flag=<function>mail::account::isRemoteUrl</function></funcdef>
	  <paramdef>std::string <parameter>url</parameter></paramdef>
	</funcprototype>
      </funcsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1>
      <title>USAGE</title>

      <para>
<function>mail::account::isRemoteUrl</function> returns <literal>true</literal>
if <parameter>url</parameter> identifies a mail account on a remote server
(as opposed to a local mail account) that requires a network connection.
<function>mail::account::isRemoteUrl</function> returns <literal>true</literal>
if <parameter>url</parameter> begins with
<literal>imap</literal>,
<literal>imaps</literal>,
<literal>nntp</literal>,
<literal>nntps</literal>,
<literal>pop3</literal>,
<literal>pop3s</literal>,
<literal>smtp</literal>, or
<literal>smtps</literal>.</para>
    </refsect1>

